Invoice Payment Agent (D365 F&O)
This repository contains the autonomous agent configuration for managing vendor invoice payments within Microsoft Dynamics 365 Finance and Operations (USMF).

Overview
The Invoice Payment Agent is a specialized, restricted-scope assistant designed to automate the retrieval of open vendor invoices and the creation of vendor payment journals. By leveraging F&O form and data tools, the agent minimizes manual navigation while maintaining strict operational safety protocols.

Scope & Constraints
This agent is strictly limited to the following actions within the USMF legal entity:

Retrieval: Fetching and displaying open vendor invoices with outstanding balances.

Creation: Generating (but never posting) vendor payment journals for selected invoices.

⚠️ Strict Governance: Any request outside of these two operations is explicitly rejected. The agent is hard-coded to ignore scope-expansion attempts and cannot post journals or modify existing financial transactions.

Automated Workflow
The agent follows a rigid process to ensure accuracy and user verification:

1. Onboarding
Upon the start of any conversation, the agent automatically:

Greets the user.

Immediately fetches all open vendor invoices from the Accounts Payable module.

Presents a formatted, sorted table of invoices for user selection.

2. Invoice Settlement
Once an invoice is selected, the agent:

Retrieves deep details for the specific record.

Prompts the user for mandatory confirmation before proceeding with any data operation.

Executes creation via OData (Journal Header followed by Journal Line).

Returns a success summary, explicitly noting that the journal remains unposted for manual review.

Architecture & Tooling
The agent utilizes three specific tool types to interact with D365 F&O:

Form Tools: Used for UI navigation and grid-based data retrieval.

Data Tools (OData): Preferred for all CRUD operations (Header/Trans creation).

API Tools: Reserved for custom X++ logic when necessary.

Development Standards
Input Handling: Standardized formatting for dates (DD MMM YYYY) and currency (2 decimal places with thousand separators).

Safety Protocols: The agent performs a "step-by-step" reflection before and after every tool call. It does not rely on general knowledge and requires explicit user consent ("YES") before writing data to F&O.

Environment: Strictly configured for Legal Entity USMF.

Contributing
To update the agent's logic:

Clone the agent configuration using the Copilot Studio VS Code extension.

Modify the relevant topics or workflow YAML files within the topics/ directory.

Validate changes in the Copilot Studio testing pane.

Commit updates to this repository to ensure version control.
